.TH "rdma_query_gid_table" 9 "rdma_query_gid_table" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rdma_query_gid_table \- Reads GID table entries of all the ports of a device up to max_entries.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" rdma_query_gid_table
.BI "(struct ib_device *device "  ","
.BI "struct ib_uverbs_gid_entry *entries "  ","
.BI "size_t max_entries "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "device" 12
The device to query.
.IP "entries" 12
Entries where GID entries are returned.
.IP "max_entries" 12
Maximum number of entries that can be returned.
Entries array must be allocated to hold max_entries number of entries.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns number of entries on success or appropriate error code.
